<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🧊 M003 Extension 2 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Pixel-Art Mob Heads (x, y) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Extension (after Week 3) · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>Copy <strong>two mob heads</strong> with <strong>(x, y)</strong> — a <strong>creeper</strong> and a <strong>piglin</strong>. x is <strong>across</strong>, y is <strong>up</strong>. Both heads already stand in front of you in the world — look at them, then build yours from the grid.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🔴 Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (red block) every run. Move your feet, move your picture.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each set. Write what you will see.</p>
<pre><code>place green block at (4, 11)
place green block at (5, 11)
place green block at (10, 11)
place green block at (11, 11)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Creeper eyes. One line, or two pairs?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>place black block at (6, 6)
place black block at (6, 7)
place black block at (6, 8)
place black block at (6, 9)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>All share x = 6. Across or up? Which number changes?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>place green block at (6, 8)
place black block at (6, 8)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Same (x, y). Green, black, or both? Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Fix each one. Then say why it was wrong.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — Creeper eyes should be (4, 11) and (10, 11). Both land in the same spot.</p>
<pre><code>place black block at (4, 11)
place black block at (4, 11)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — Piglin eye should be (5, 10). The numbers are swapped.</p>
<pre><code>place dark block at (10, 5)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — Code is correct, but the creeper came out two blocks too high.</p>
<pre><code>(the code matched the grid)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What did your friend forget before pressing run?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Pick <strong>one</strong> head. Read each colored square's (x, y) and build it. Top numbers = <strong>x</strong>, side numbers = <strong>y</strong>. Done early? Build the other.</p>
